WEBVTT

1
00:00:11.136 --> 00:00:12.849
The rap world
has been shaken again.

2
00:00:12.929 --> 00:00:14.931
this time by the violent
death of the performer

3
00:00:15.015 --> 00:00:16.766
known as Notorious B.I.G.

4
00:00:16.850 --> 00:00:19.185
He went
down in a hail of gunfire

5
00:00:19.310 --> 00:00:20.687
on a public street.

6
00:00:20.770 --> 00:00:23.189
His death comes
just six months after his rival.

7
00:00:23.314 --> 00:00:25.775
West Coast rapper. Tupac
Shakur. was assassinated.

8
00:00:25.859 --> 00:00:29.821
Last six months. hip-hop
probably lost its two biggest stars.

9
00:00:31.031 --> 00:00:32.115
It's just a tragedy.

10
00:00:35.326 --> 00:00:40.040
After B.I.G
passed. I got this call from Puff.

11
00:00:42.876 --> 00:00:45.336
I remember he
sounded so depressed.

12
00:00:46.880 --> 00:00:49.215
He said that he hadn't
left the house in days.

13
00:00:49.340 --> 00:00:52.969
He was one of the only
people besides my mother

14
00:00:53.053 --> 00:00:55.764
that really cared about me.

15
00:00:55.889 --> 00:00:57.644
And he said. "People
have been knocking on my door.

16
00:00:57.724 --> 00:01:00.894
I've just been here by
myself. I ain't eat nothing."

17
00:01:00.977 --> 00:01:03.146
And he was almost
sounding suicidal.

18
00:01:05.397 --> 00:01:07.400
I just tried to talk some light

19
00:01:07.484 --> 00:01:10.987
into what I could hear was
a time of a lot of darkness.

20
00:01:11.071 --> 00:01:13.471
And just tell him that. you
know. you have a lot to live for.

21
00:01:16.159 --> 00:01:19.454
Then. I remember days
later. him calling me back.

22
00:01:19.579 --> 00:01:22.082
"Yo. G. come by
the studio after work."

23
00:01:23.374 --> 00:01:25.710
And he played Every
Breath You Take.

24
00:01:27.212 --> 00:01:30.131
And he was playing it loud.

25
00:01:33.885 --> 00:01:35.637
He was just into it
and just played it.

26
00:01:35.762 --> 00:01:37.347
and kept playing
and dancing to it.

27
00:01:37.430 --> 00:01:38.765
And I remember him asking me.

28
00:01:38.848 --> 00:01:39.936
"What do you think?
What do you think?

29
00:01:40.016 --> 00:01:41.601
Do you think people
would rock to this?"

30
00:01:42.519 --> 00:01:44.104
I didn't know what to say.

31
00:01:44.187 --> 00:01:48.817
Because. you know. Every
Breath You Take was so white pop.

32
00:01:48.942 --> 00:01:51.820
I couldn't hear it or couldn't
envision it at the time.

33
00:01:51.945 --> 00:01:55.865
But I'm glad to see that his
creative juices were flowing again.

34
00:01:55.949 --> 00:01:58.701
And then I'll Be
Missing You was huge.

35
00:02:05.416 --> 00:02:07.043
It was a runaway hit.

36
00:02:07.127 --> 00:02:09.878
it captured the emotions
and the grief at the time

37
00:02:09.963 --> 00:02:13.133
that was happening to the
African American community.

38
00:02:13.258 --> 00:02:16.803
We just knew this was helping
us remember Biggie in some way.

39
00:02:18.138 --> 00:02:20.014
On a Sunday morning...

40
00:02:20.140 --> 00:02:22.767
headed to church. and I'll
Be Missing You came on.

41
00:02:23.810 --> 00:02:25.395
It made it to the
gospel station.

42
00:02:25.478 --> 00:02:29.357
and that's when I
knew who he was.

43
00:02:29.482 --> 00:02:31.317
It was like an amazing grace

44
00:02:31.442 --> 00:02:33.528
for the hip-hop generation.

45
00:02:33.653 --> 00:02:36.781
When people hear that.
it still touches people.

46
00:02:37.824 --> 00:02:40.326
He could see things

47
00:02:40.410 --> 00:02:43.329
for the culture that other
people just couldn't see.

48
00:02:43.454 --> 00:02:47.000
And I remember just thinking.
like. "This man is a genius."

49
00:02:48.168 --> 00:02:51.254
But while this genius man
was developing his talent.

50
00:02:51.337 --> 00:02:55.091
what else was not developed

51
00:02:55.175 --> 00:02:56.342
that he became somebody

52
00:02:56.467 --> 00:02:57.844
who could create a lot of pain?

53
00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:05.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

54
00:03:24.871 --> 00:03:26.539
One of my big motivations

55
00:03:26.664 --> 00:03:28.041
of wanting to be a part of this.

56
00:03:28.124 --> 00:03:29.250
it's one of those situations

57
00:03:29.375 --> 00:03:34.464
where you just have
no idea in real time

58
00:03:34.547 --> 00:03:36.299
that you're working
with somebody

59
00:03:36.382 --> 00:03:39.302
that ends up changing the world.

60
00:03:39.385 --> 00:03:42.889
It is hard to overstate
how important

61
00:03:43.014 --> 00:03:46.809
Bad Boy and the Puff
sound was to the '90s.

62
00:03:49.395 --> 00:03:51.898
I remember a time
where you could listen

63
00:03:52.023 --> 00:03:54.234
to the radio for an hour

64
00:03:54.317 --> 00:03:57.737
and hear nothing but Bad
Boy artists for that entire hour.

65
00:03:57.862 --> 00:03:59.159
Diddy knew how to create

66
00:03:59.239 --> 00:04:00.907
what Black culture
wanted to see.

67
00:04:01.032 --> 00:04:02.575
what mainstream
culture wanted to see.

68
00:04:02.700 --> 00:04:05.078
what American
culture wanted to see.

69
00:04:05.203 --> 00:04:07.497
Puffy started to
work with producers

70
00:04:07.580 --> 00:04:10.583
that.. that were using
samples lifted from records

71
00:04:10.667 --> 00:04:14.295
and then taking some of the
vocals. and interpolating them.

72
00:04:14.420 --> 00:04:16.339
Puffy took that to
yet another level.

73
00:04:16.422 --> 00:04:19.841
to sing hooks on top
of the... the rhymes.

74
00:04:26.057 --> 00:04:29.686
I feel like Combs and crew
were just throwing things

75
00:04:29.769 --> 00:04:33.481
against the wall. and
everything was sticking.

76
00:04:33.606 --> 00:04:35.858
He was having a relationship

77
00:04:35.942 --> 00:04:40.280
with product and audiences
from the beginning.

78
00:04:40.405 --> 00:04:42.615
But nobody really could see that

79
00:04:42.740 --> 00:04:45.034
until the empire got so big.

80
00:04:45.118 --> 00:04:48.538
they was like. "this is what
he's been trying to do all this time."

81
00:04:48.621 --> 00:04:51.499
It was interesting to see Puffy

82
00:04:51.624 --> 00:04:55.044
move into other
areas other than music.

83
00:04:55.128 --> 00:04:58.881
It was just inevitable for
the clothing to be next.

84
00:04:58.965 --> 00:05:00.178
We call it urban high fashion.

85
00:05:00.258 --> 00:05:03.052
We combined the look
of the European clothes

86
00:05:03.136 --> 00:05:04.846
to... to the urban style.

87
00:05:04.971 --> 00:05:07.227
which is a little bit loose. a
little bit baggy. a little bit more.

88
00:05:07.307 --> 00:05:08.308
has a better fit. too.

89
00:05:09.434 --> 00:05:13.646
Sean John was
incredibly successful.

90
00:05:13.771 --> 00:05:17.817
You saw it go from
it's just worn on artists.

91
00:05:17.942 --> 00:05:21.738
to it's worn by
influential people

92
00:05:21.821 --> 00:05:23.823
in the cultural scene...

93
00:05:23.906 --> 00:05:27.744
to. like. a dad in Missouri

94
00:05:27.827 --> 00:05:29.996
who's got a Sean John shirt.

95
00:05:30.079 --> 00:05:32.498
Could he name any
Puff Daddy record?

96
00:05:32.582 --> 00:05:35.209
No. But he knows who Puff is.

97
00:05:35.335 --> 00:05:37.337
and he's rocking the Sean John.

98
00:05:37.462 --> 00:05:38.549
The clothing brand.

99
00:05:38.629 --> 00:05:40.229
now. at this point.
transcends the music.

100
00:05:40.340 --> 00:05:42.175
and it becomes part
of this mythology...

101
00:05:43.092 --> 00:05:44.844
that Sean Combs begins to build.

102
00:05:46.179 --> 00:05:48.348
I remember going
with him to Macy's.

103
00:05:48.473 --> 00:05:51.351
and we were up in... in the
boardroom with all the executives.

104
00:05:51.434 --> 00:05:53.234
and they treated him
like he was Ralph Lauren.

105
00:05:53.353 --> 00:05:54.604
He was a king.

106
00:05:55.688 --> 00:05:57.273
There was nobody
in New York City

107
00:05:57.357 --> 00:05:59.525
that Diddy could
not get in touch with.

108
00:05:59.650 --> 00:06:02.904
We used to call him
Puff the Magic Dragon.

109
00:06:03.029 --> 00:06:04.364
and we said that with love.

110
00:06:04.447 --> 00:06:06.240
He was so much fun.

111
00:06:06.366 --> 00:06:07.617
He threw the best parties.

112
00:06:09.369 --> 00:06:13.289
I remember seeing celebrities
just let their hair down.

113
00:06:13.373 --> 00:06:16.042
I remember seeing Mary J. Blige.

114
00:06:16.125 --> 00:06:17.125
Ashton.

115
00:06:18.461 --> 00:06:21.381
I mean. it was Gatsbyesque.

116
00:06:22.048 --> 00:06:23.674
It was like in the movies.

117
00:06:24.300 --> 00:06:26.928
They were huge.

118
00:06:27.053 --> 00:06:32.475
And part of Sean's move with the parties
is not just a party for party's sake.

119
00:06:32.558 --> 00:06:37.063
but really to embellish
who he is in the culture.

120
00:06:37.188 --> 00:06:39.607
Who can come to Sean
Combs' White Party.

121
00:06:39.732 --> 00:06:41.234
in the Hamptons.

122
00:06:42.360 --> 00:06:44.320
It speaks more to
a new Black money.

123
00:06:44.404 --> 00:06:46.406
It carried a different
kind of cachet.

124
00:06:47.865 --> 00:06:51.953
What we heard. even at the
time that they were taking place.

125
00:06:52.078 --> 00:06:54.372
was that there was
a lot of debauchery.

126
00:06:58.084 --> 00:06:59.919
Puffy would have women laid out

127
00:07:00.002 --> 00:07:01.754
and have food on their bodies.

128
00:07:03.673 --> 00:07:06.008
These are things that were
photographed and publicized.

129
00:07:06.092 --> 00:07:08.052
and just viewed as kind
of grand and opulent.

130
00:07:11.264 --> 00:07:13.307
I started
blogging in the early 2000s.

131
00:07:13.433 --> 00:07:15.935
I started getting reports
about the type of things

132
00:07:16.018 --> 00:07:18.187
that would happen
at these parties.

133
00:07:18.271 --> 00:07:21.441
I was hearing
about illicit drugs.

134
00:07:21.524 --> 00:07:25.361
I was hearing about
sexual escapades.

135
00:07:25.445 --> 00:07:29.073
I always have decisions
to make about stories.

136
00:07:29.740 --> 00:07:32.618
And for a long time.

137
00:07:32.743 --> 00:07:35.621
when it came to things
pertaining to Diddy.

138
00:07:35.705 --> 00:07:40.710
I wouldn't run certain things
because I feared retribution.

139
00:07:40.793 --> 00:07:43.880
He felt and seemed
like he was invincible.

140
00:07:46.424 --> 00:07:47.970
I mean. I work.
like. 20 hours a day.

141
00:07:48.050 --> 00:07:49.719
and I feel as a young Black man.

142
00:07:49.802 --> 00:07:52.680
about anything I put
my mind to. I could do.

143
00:07:52.805 --> 00:07:54.974
Whatever I put into it.
I'm gonna get out of it.

144
00:07:55.057 --> 00:07:59.061
And I put 150%. 200%
into anything I do. always.

145
00:07:59.145 --> 00:08:01.481
Diddy really personified

146
00:08:01.564 --> 00:08:04.734
Black excellence
and authenticity.

147
00:08:04.817 --> 00:08:05.860
He was succeeding.

148
00:08:05.985 --> 00:08:09.655
and he was doing it in
an authentically Black way.

149
00:08:11.991 --> 00:08:16.245
So. he was really someone
that a lot of us looked up to.

150
00:08:18.998 --> 00:08:21.250
But with
money. he got more gangster.

151
00:08:21.334 --> 00:08:22.668
he got meaner.

152
00:08:22.793 --> 00:08:24.504
He got more no nonsense.

153
00:08:26.297 --> 00:08:28.591
He couldn't let the
foot off nobody's neck.

154
00:08:28.674 --> 00:08:31.677
His foot got harder on necks.

155
00:08:31.761 --> 00:08:34.597
Because he knew.
"Yo. if I slip one inch.

156
00:08:34.679 --> 00:08:38.100
if I show one inch
of weakness...

157
00:08:39.684 --> 00:08:41.020
they gonna take it from me."

158
00:08:52.532 --> 00:08:54.784
I definitely
think there's a huge

159
00:08:54.867 --> 00:08:58.996
reflection of his childhood
to who he is today.

160
00:09:01.874 --> 00:09:03.876
Sean started
breathing rarefied air

161
00:09:03.960 --> 00:09:05.419
before he even realized it.

162
00:09:05.545 --> 00:09:07.046
Janice wanted a prince.

163
00:09:07.171 --> 00:09:08.589
and the last thing
she wants to do

164
00:09:08.714 --> 00:09:10.883
is to have her prince
making her look bad.

165
00:09:12.051 --> 00:09:15.054
And one thing about
anybody from Harlem.

166
00:09:15.179 --> 00:09:17.390
if you're soft. you're done.

167
00:09:18.224 --> 00:09:19.684
That's just the mentality.

168
00:09:22.061 --> 00:09:24.814
'Cause. mind you.
she lost her husband.

169
00:09:24.897 --> 00:09:27.108
Now. she's got this kid
that looks just like him.

170
00:09:27.233 --> 00:09:28.233
That's emotions.

171
00:09:29.527 --> 00:09:31.782
Someday. she'll wake up. she
might be mad when she sees him

172
00:09:31.862 --> 00:09:34.365
because she sees
what used to be Melvin.

173
00:09:35.533 --> 00:09:39.161
So. Sean's mom
had to fill the shoes

174
00:09:39.245 --> 00:09:41.330
of Sean's dad and mom.

175
00:09:41.414 --> 00:09:46.502
And I'm sure everything from Janice's
way of raising him was coming from love.

176
00:09:48.170 --> 00:09:50.089
But there were
times that I would see

177
00:09:50.214 --> 00:09:53.676
Janice's personality
go from hot to cold.

178
00:09:53.759 --> 00:09:55.678
And he had to be
on the receiving end

179
00:09:55.761 --> 00:09:58.180
of a hot night or a cold night.

180
00:10:00.391 --> 00:10:03.019
Janice didn't take
no shit. None at all.

181
00:10:03.102 --> 00:10:05.104
She ruled with her iron fist.

182
00:10:05.187 --> 00:10:06.439
Better get right.

183
00:10:06.522 --> 00:10:08.803
And. you know. a lot of
times. Sean couldn't get it right.

184
00:10:09.358 --> 00:10:11.277
Couldn't get nothing right.

185
00:10:11.402 --> 00:10:13.529
And she didn't let him
get away with nothing.

186
00:10:13.613 --> 00:10:14.488
Nothing.

187
00:10:14.614 --> 00:10:16.449
And that's how it
was in Sean's house.

188
00:10:17.783 --> 00:10:19.952
If he did something
wrong. he'd get his ass beat.

189
00:10:20.036 --> 00:10:21.120
simple as that.

190
00:10:22.622 --> 00:10:26.417
She knew that he
wasn't hard enough.

191
00:10:29.378 --> 00:10:31.797
In those days.
that was the order.

192
00:10:31.881 --> 00:10:33.549
You know. you
didn't spare the rod.

193
00:10:37.261 --> 00:10:38.971
I remember that real vivid.

194
00:10:43.601 --> 00:10:45.811
Especially if you don't
know if the punishment..

195
00:10:46.771 --> 00:10:48.147
Really fits the crime.

196
00:10:50.316 --> 00:10:53.194
Wasn't my place to say
whether it was or not. but to me.

197
00:10:53.319 --> 00:10:55.154
it didn't seem
necessary at times.

198
00:10:58.074 --> 00:11:00.660
So. he's learning how
to be a wolf the hard way.

199
00:11:02.286 --> 00:11:04.580
For him. it wasn't as easy.

200
00:11:04.664 --> 00:11:06.624
It took a while for him
to become his wolf.

201
00:11:08.167 --> 00:11:09.710
Goddamn. when he became a wolf.

202
00:11:09.835 --> 00:11:11.253
it was no turning back.

203
00:11:16.467 --> 00:11:19.178
As part of our investigation.
we looked at the history

204
00:11:19.303 --> 00:11:22.723
of Diddy's behavior
and relationships.

205
00:11:22.848 --> 00:11:27.186
We have found that there has
been a clear pattern of abuse

206
00:11:27.269 --> 00:11:29.105
since the beginning.
since he was a teenager.

207
00:11:31.357 --> 00:11:34.360
I noticed how
he interacted with his girls.

208
00:11:34.443 --> 00:11:36.696
and it was way different
than I interacted with my girls.

209
00:11:36.779 --> 00:11:38.114
It was more physical.

210
00:11:40.157 --> 00:11:43.327
It was more
self-esteem lowering.

211
00:11:44.203 --> 00:11:45.413
It was a lot of insecurity.

212
00:11:45.538 --> 00:11:47.873
It was a lot of "who
you're dealing with.

213
00:11:47.998 --> 00:11:50.793
I heard you was
here. I don't like that."

214
00:11:50.876 --> 00:11:52.757
You know. a lot of girls
got thrown out of the car.

215
00:11:52.837 --> 00:11:54.714
Sometimes. I would
drive his girlfriends' home

216
00:11:54.797 --> 00:11:55.965
to wherever they live

217
00:11:56.048 --> 00:11:58.801
because they...
they had a fight.

218
00:11:58.884 --> 00:12:00.386
So. you know. I was the go-to.

219
00:12:00.511 --> 00:12:04.890
I was the "Timmy.
what's wrong with him?"

220
00:12:04.974 --> 00:12:09.103
It just never
seemed to get better

221
00:12:09.228 --> 00:12:11.021
with him and relationships.

222
00:12:15.526 --> 00:12:19.321
One of Combs' first
public relationships was with Misa Hylton.

223
00:12:19.405 --> 00:12:21.907
who also grew up in
the Mount Vernon area

224
00:12:22.032 --> 00:12:23.993
and was a teenager
when they started dating.

225
00:12:25.536 --> 00:12:28.247
Any girl that's
with Sean has to be fixed.

226
00:12:29.832 --> 00:12:31.834
To his specs.

227
00:12:31.917 --> 00:12:35.004
Sean looked at Misa
as his blank canvas.

228
00:12:35.087 --> 00:12:36.087
like. "my God.

229
00:12:37.089 --> 00:12:39.592
Yo. dawg. I could
fix her. Ooh!."

230
00:12:39.675 --> 00:12:40.926
It was his project.

231
00:12:42.219 --> 00:12:45.765
So. Misa became
somebody in the game.

232
00:12:46.932 --> 00:12:52.146
When you think of the most
classic. iconic '90s looks.

233
00:12:52.271 --> 00:12:54.690
Misa Hylton was behind them.

234
00:12:54.774 --> 00:12:57.443
She was a visionary
in her own right.

235
00:12:57.568 --> 00:13:01.155
creating some of the
best-known looks for Lil' Kim.

236
00:13:01.280 --> 00:13:03.824
She really created the mold

237
00:13:03.949 --> 00:13:06.035
of what an artist at
that time looked like.

238
00:13:09.288 --> 00:13:12.625
My sister.
Sonya. and Misa were close friends.

239
00:13:13.626 --> 00:13:17.129
I heard that Puff was
putting his hands on Mis

240
00:13:17.254 --> 00:13:19.715
in '89. '88.'89.

241
00:13:20.966 --> 00:13:22.676
So. at that time. I
heard a few occasions.

242
00:13:22.802 --> 00:13:25.137
he was physical with Misa.

243
00:13:25.221 --> 00:13:26.475
They fight all the time.

244
00:13:26.555 --> 00:13:28.682
They argue like cats and dogs.

245
00:13:28.808 --> 00:13:32.478
And yeah. I've definitely seen
them put hands on each other.

246
00:13:33.604 --> 00:13:36.732
I remember when
Misa was pregnant.

247
00:13:36.816 --> 00:13:38.567
Sean was in his early 20s.

248
00:13:38.651 --> 00:13:40.236
This dude is a millionaire now.

249
