in doubt.

499
00:27:04.289 --> 00:27:07.125
In light of the
current atmosphere.

500
00:27:07.250 --> 00:27:08.293
with the lawsuits

501
00:27:08.376 --> 00:27:10.295
and all of the stories
that have come out.

502
00:27:10.378 --> 00:27:12.088
I knew it was time
for me to speak up.

503
00:27:15.175 --> 00:27:19.471
This is something
that was in my past.

504
00:27:19.596 --> 00:27:21.514
and it belongs in the past.

505
00:27:21.640 --> 00:27:26.144
But I can no longer
just remain silent.

506
00:27:26.269 --> 00:27:29.564
This is the first time I've
shared my story on camera.

507
00:27:33.943 --> 00:27:38.239
I started driving for
Mr. Combs in 1999.

508
00:27:39.491 --> 00:27:43.370
On December 26th. I was informed

509
00:27:43.495 --> 00:27:46.665
that Mr. Combs would
be requiring my services.

510
00:27:47.832 --> 00:27:54.130
I drove down to his studio
to pick up Mr. Combs

511
00:27:54.214 --> 00:27:55.965
and Jennifer.

512
00:27:57.467 --> 00:28:00.053
Mr. Combs got in the vehicle

513
00:28:00.178 --> 00:28:03.515
and I happened at one point
to glance over my shoulder.

514
00:28:04.474 --> 00:28:06.851
and I noticed him
holding a black handgun.

515
00:28:08.269 --> 00:28:11.022
No words were exchanged.
We made eye contact.

516
00:28:11.147 --> 00:28:13.358
He said nothing. I said nothing.

517
00:28:13.483 --> 00:28:17.070
And I proceeded en
route to Club New York.

518
00:28:21.533 --> 00:28:24.202
I hadn't been in the
club scene or anything

519
00:28:24.285 --> 00:28:26.579
for the better part of a month.

520
00:28:26.705 --> 00:28:28.373
Honestly. I really
wasn't going out.

521
00:28:28.498 --> 00:28:31.376
but one of my good friends
was a party promoter.

522
00:28:31.501 --> 00:28:32.877
She wanted me to come out

523
00:28:32.961 --> 00:28:34.441
and I wanted to
support her endeavors.

524
00:28:37.966 --> 00:28:39.718
Puff arrives with his entourage

525
00:28:39.843 --> 00:28:43.054
and they go to the VIP section.

526
00:28:43.138 --> 00:28:45.223
There started to
be a crowd walking through

527
00:28:45.348 --> 00:28:46.891
coming from the dance floor.

528
00:28:46.975 --> 00:28:49.686
People are gravitating
towards the VIP section.

529
00:28:49.769 --> 00:28:52.564
And there were some
people who just...

530
00:28:52.689 --> 00:28:54.649
say. "This guy is showing off."

531
00:28:56.067 --> 00:28:58.695
People were telling Puffy.
you know. "You ain't shit.

532
00:28:58.778 --> 00:29:00.572
You ain't this. You ain't that."

533
00:29:00.697 --> 00:29:04.200
The next thing you know.
we see pushing and shoving.

534
00:29:04.284 --> 00:29:06.077
The crowd is
swaying. You hear...

535
00:29:06.953 --> 00:29:08.580
like. angered voices.

536
00:29:09.622 --> 00:29:11.416
And he bumped into Puffy

537
00:29:11.499 --> 00:29:14.419
and Shyne just uttered.

538
00:29:14.544 --> 00:29:16.421
"I'm tired of this shit."

539
00:29:16.504 --> 00:29:19.966
I start to see Puffy
and Shyne backing up.

540
00:29:20.091 --> 00:29:25.096
backing away from the area
of the melee towards the door.

541
00:29:25.221 --> 00:29:27.932
And I see them
reach in their waists.

542
00:29:28.016 --> 00:29:30.477
I turned to tell my friends.
"my God. Let's go!

543
00:29:30.602 --> 00:29:31.603
Let's go!

544
00:29:31.728 --> 00:29:34.439
Watch out! Something's
getting ready to go down."

545
00:29:34.564 --> 00:29:37.650
And just as I turn
back and I look at them.

546
00:29:37.776 --> 00:29:40.779
I see them both holding
guns. and God said to me.

547
00:29:40.904 --> 00:29:43.615
"Be still. You're
about to get hit."

548
00:29:43.740 --> 00:29:45.450
And I just see the muzzle flash.

549
00:29:45.575 --> 00:29:46.575
Pow. pow.

550
00:29:51.456 --> 00:29:54.459
I grabbed my face because
I instantly feel this hot...

551
00:29:55.460 --> 00:29:58.129
torching flame on my face.

552
00:29:58.213 --> 00:30:00.799
And I turned my head
and I'm like. "my God...

553
00:30:02.509 --> 00:30:03.718
I got shot in my face."

554
00:30:05.887 --> 00:30:07.806
I felt myself separated

555
00:30:07.931 --> 00:30:11.434
and the cold air rushed
towards my chest

556
00:30:11.518 --> 00:30:12.518
and passed through me.

557
00:30:12.602 --> 00:30:13.882
I could feel it pass through me.

558
00:30:14.854 --> 00:30:17.023
I was certain that I
was going to be dead

559
00:30:17.148 --> 00:30:18.316
at that moment.

560
00:30:18.399 --> 00:30:21.611
because I didn't think a human
could lose that much blood

561
00:30:21.694 --> 00:30:22.946
and still be alive.

562
00:30:23.863 --> 00:30:24.863
And I just...

563
00:30:32.413 --> 00:30:34.958
I knew my life was never
going to be the same again.

564
00:30:43.132 --> 00:30:44.092
At that moment.

565
00:30:44.175 --> 00:30:46.511
Puffy is trying to
make the great escape.

566
00:30:46.636 --> 00:30:48.346
It's just chaos.

567
00:30:48.429 --> 00:30:52.976
Shyne was
in custody of the police.

568
00:30:53.059 --> 00:30:56.688
Mr. Combs. his
security guy. Wolf.

569
00:30:56.813 --> 00:30:59.232
and Jennifer Lopez comes out.

570
00:31:01.067 --> 00:31:04.571
I'm instructed to. "Let's
go. Let's get out of here."

571
00:31:06.364 --> 00:31:09.200
I was driving
through the red light.

572
00:31:09.325 --> 00:31:11.536
evading the police.

573
00:31:11.619 --> 00:31:14.706
I'd noticed the rear
passenger window

574
00:31:14.789 --> 00:31:16.875
over my right shoulder
had been opened.

575
00:31:17.834 --> 00:31:21.421
I later found out that
was when Mr. Combs

576
00:31:21.546 --> 00:31:24.591
apparently tossed his
weapon out of the vehicle.

577
00:31:26.593 --> 00:31:29.846
Mr. Combs and
Wolf were screaming.

578
00:31:29.929 --> 00:31:31.890
"Don't stop! Don't
stop! Don't stop!"

579
00:31:32.515 --> 00:31:34.058
Seated next to me.

580
00:31:34.183 --> 00:31:39.814
I noticed another gun
in Wolf's waistband.

581
00:31:41.024 --> 00:31:43.610
And then a cruiser had come out.

582
00:31:43.735 --> 00:31:45.695
blocking Eighth Avenue.

583
00:31:47.488 --> 00:31:50.533
And I said. "Chase is over."

584
00:31:53.870 --> 00:31:57.749
We are all escorted
into the police precinct.

585
00:31:59.709 --> 00:32:03.504
That's when out of
the side of his mouth.

586
00:32:04.088 --> 00:32:06.424
Mr. Combs says.

587
00:32:06.549 --> 00:32:10.553
"Yo. I'll give you
$50.000 to take the gun."

588
00:32:11.638 --> 00:32:14.641
And he was saying this
under his breath. of course.

589
00:32:14.766 --> 00:32:17.393
because we were right in
front of the desk sergeant.

590
00:32:20.939 --> 00:32:27.445
Puffy reaches onto
his pinky and says.

591
00:32:27.528 --> 00:32:31.282
"I will give you
this diamond ring.

592
00:32:31.366 --> 00:32:35.453
which is worth $300.000.
to hold as collateral

593
00:32:35.536 --> 00:32:37.538
if you don't think I'm
good for the money."

594
00:32:40.249 --> 00:32:43.294
I did not want
to take the bribe.

595
00:32:43.419 --> 00:32:46.589
but the phrase
on the street is...

596
00:32:47.173 --> 00:32:48.967
snitches get stitches.

597
00:32:51.302 --> 00:32:52.595
Go. go. go. go. go!

598
00:32:54.013 --> 00:32:55.693
- There go Puff.
- Puff!

599
00:32:56.265 --> 00:32:57.767
Before it even began.

600
00:32:57.850 --> 00:32:59.477
the trial of Sean "Puffy" Combs

601
00:32:59.560 --> 00:33:01.771
had turned into
a tabloid torrent.

602
00:33:01.854 --> 00:33:03.026
A high-profile case

603
00:33:03.106 --> 00:33:05.316
that's attracted
overwhelming support

604
00:33:05.441 --> 00:33:07.485
from Combs' diehard fans.

605
00:33:08.444 --> 00:33:09.654
Not guilty!

606
00:33:09.737 --> 00:33:12.281
Puffy's future
is in the hands of 12 jurors

607
00:33:12.365 --> 00:33:14.492
and faces up to
15 years in prison

608
00:33:14.617 --> 00:33:17.495
on charges of weapons
possession and bribery.

609
00:33:17.578 --> 00:33:20.999
Sean Combs. in the early 2000s

610
00:33:21.124 --> 00:33:24.002
is about selling a
lifestyle. selling a brand.

611
00:33:24.127 --> 00:33:26.629
So he really had to
protect his reputation

612
00:33:26.713 --> 00:33:31.134
and his freedom at all
costs in this moment.

613
00:33:31.217 --> 00:33:32.513
His high-powered defense team.

614
00:33:32.593 --> 00:33:33.928
including Johnnie Cochran...

615
00:33:34.012 --> 00:33:36.556
Johnnie Cochran. he's
known as the O.J. Simpson lawyer.

616
00:33:36.681 --> 00:33:39.350
If it doesn't fit.
you must acquit.

617
00:33:39.475 --> 00:33:41.894
There was another attorney by
the name of Benjamin Brafman.

618
00:33:42.020 --> 00:33:44.147
one of the top criminal
defense attorneys in the city.

619
00:33:44.230 --> 00:33:45.356
defending Puffy.

620
00:33:45.440 --> 00:33:47.567
Shyne. Wolf and Puffy.

621
00:33:47.692 --> 00:33:49.527
they all have separate lawyers.

622
00:33:49.610 --> 00:33:51.070
It was really two trials.

623
00:33:51.195 --> 00:33:54.866
It was this great
celebrity. "Puffy" Combs

624
00:33:54.991 --> 00:33:56.325
and his bodyguard.

625
00:33:57.452 --> 00:34:01.748
and Shyne. really just a
New York City teenager

626
00:34:01.873 --> 00:34:05.543
that had just signed
the deal of his life.

627
00:34:05.668 --> 00:34:08.045
From the notoriety
of the people on trial

628
00:34:08.129 --> 00:34:09.797
to the notoriety
of the attorneys.

629
00:34:11.090 --> 00:34:12.300
it was a circus.

630
00:34:15.344 --> 00:34:17.679
While he's not
accused of gunning anyone down.

631
00:34:17.764 --> 00:34:20.433
prosecutors say someone
at the club taunted Combs

632
00:34:20.558 --> 00:34:23.186
and he and fellow rapper
Jamaal "Shyne" Barrow

633
00:34:23.268 --> 00:34:25.438
pulled out guns and fired.

634
00:34:25.563 --> 00:34:28.190
Barrow's shots allegedly
injured three people.

635
00:34:29.108 --> 00:34:30.610
Puffy denied from the beginning

636
00:34:30.735 --> 00:34:33.279
that he ever fired a gun.

637
00:34:33.404 --> 00:34:36.574
that he ever had any
guns in his possession.

638
00:34:36.657 --> 00:34:39.409
I want to make this 100% clear.

639
00:34:39.494 --> 00:34:44.123
I had nothing to do with
a shooting in this club.

640
00:34:44.248 --> 00:34:46.250
During the trial.
Puffy is looking around.

641
00:34:46.375 --> 00:34:47.710
he's very confident.

642
00:34:47.793 --> 00:34:49.795
"Hey. I allegedly
paid off people.

643
00:34:49.920 --> 00:34:51.422
so I have nothing
to worry about."

644
00:34:51.547 --> 00:34:52.757
But then...

645
00:34:52.882 --> 00:34:55.467
Liar. liar. pants on fire.

646
00:34:55.592 --> 00:34:57.637
I decided to testify.

647
00:34:57.762 --> 00:35:00.765
I was the prosecution's
main witness.

648
00:35:00.890 --> 00:35:05.436
The most damaging
testimony so far from his former driver.

649
00:35:05.520 --> 00:35:08.064
Yes. I was nervous
about cooperating.

650
00:35:08.564 --> 00:35:10.441
but I had to.

651
00:35:10.525 --> 00:35:12.530
You have to stand up for
what's right in this world.

652
00:35:12.610 --> 00:35:15.488
Fenderson
testified Combs had a gun.

653
00:35:15.613 --> 00:35:21.119
I was recanting my statement
and no longer going along

654
00:35:21.202 --> 00:35:24.956
with their scheme to
take ownership of the gun.

655
00:35:26.165 --> 00:35:27.795
But Fenderson
wasn't the only witness

656
00:35:27.875 --> 00:35:30.253
to put a gun in Combs' hand.

657
00:35:30.336 --> 00:35:32.130
When I had to testify.

658
00:35:32.213 --> 00:35:34.423
I said. "I saw without
a doubt who shot me.

659
00:35:34.507 --> 00:35:36.342
I was shot by Sean
'Puffy' Combs."

660
00:35:37.969 --> 00:35:39.512
I've said that ever
since that day.

661
00:35:39.637 --> 00:35:43.641
I never once ever changed that.

662
00:35:43.766 --> 00:35:46.185
modified it. modulated
it in any way.

663
00:35:47.270 --> 00:35:49.355
And I never
expected to be a part...

664
00:35:50.439 --> 00:35:52.817
of such a reckless
act of violence.

665
00:35:52.942 --> 00:35:55.444
Natania. she had
the kind of resilience

666
00:35:55.528 --> 00:35:56.779
and defiance...

667
00:35:56.863 --> 00:35:58.364
My heart was with her.

668
00:35:58.489 --> 00:36:00.658
The defense
described a two-prong approach.

669
00:36:00.741 --> 00:36:02.118
First. calling their
own witnesses.

670
00:36:02.201 --> 00:36:04.787
who say he didn't have
a gun at the nightclub.

671
00:36:04.871 --> 00:36:06.831
Most of the
witnesses who came up

672
00:36:06.956 --> 00:36:08.666
said. "Shyne had a gun

673
00:36:08.791 --> 00:36:11.836
and we did not see a
gun in Puffy's hand."

674
00:36:11.961 --> 00:36:13.925
And. second. discrediting
the prosecution witnesses

675
00:36:14.005 --> 00:36:15.339
who put a gun in Puffy's hand.

676
00:36:15.464 --> 00:36:17.175
The lead defense attorney.

677
00:36:17.300 --> 00:36:22.513
his cross-examination
was getting a bit aggressive.

678
00:36:22.638 --> 00:36:26.767
I says. "I'm not the one on
trial here today. Your Honor.

679
00:36:27.226 --> 00:36:28.561
He is."

680
00:36:28.686 --> 00:36:31.522
And I pointed and
glared right over at Diddy.

681
00:36:33.149 --> 00:36:35.693
Some people
said this was a conspiracy.

682
00:36:35.776 --> 00:36:37.028
People cursed me out.

683
00:36:37.153 --> 00:36:39.989
accusing me of trying to
take down a good Black man

684
00:36:40.072 --> 00:36:41.824
and destroy hip-hop.

685
00:36:41.908 --> 00:36:45.494
My heart really. truly
breaks for Natania

686
00:36:45.578 --> 00:36:47.705
and what she has been through.

687
00:36:47.788 --> 00:36:51.042
Natania deserved
nothing but compassion

688
00:36:51.125 --> 00:36:52.418
and protection.

689
00:36:52.543 --> 00:36:53.878
and the culture failed her.

690
00:36:56.130 --> 00:36:57.718
They were
ridiculing me on the air.

691
00:36:57.798 --> 00:37:00.676
saying. "Does anybody
know this one-eyed ho?

692
00:37:01.844 --> 00:37:04.513
Call us up and give
us some dirt on her."

693
00:37:04.597 --> 00:37:07.391
playing rapid succession
gunfire soundtrack

694
00:37:07.475 --> 00:37:08.935
in the background.

695
00:37:09.769 --> 00:37:11.729
I was devastated.

696
00:37:12.647 --> 00:37:14.941
Why were they doing this to me?

697
00:37:15.066 --> 00:37:17.860
After the shooting. Natania.
she was appearing on the radio

698
00:37:17.944 --> 00:37:19.237
and trying to tell her story.

699
00:37:19.362 --> 00:37:20.882
She was actually
getting death threats.

700
00:37:22.865 --> 00:37:24.036
I would look out the windows

701
00:37:24.116 --> 00:37:25.785
and there'd be blacked-out SUVs

702
00:37:25.910 --> 00:37:27.662
parked on the
corners by my house.

703
00:37:28.829 --> 00:37:32.083
Those SUVs were watching me.

704
00:37:32.166 --> 00:37:35.044
And for my own safety.
I had to be moved.

705
00:37:40.758 --> 00:37:43.928
I will never forget that day
when the verdicts were read.

706
00:37:45.388 --> 00:37:47.723
A gasp went up in the courtroom.

707
00:37:57.316 --> 00:37:59.902
I'm just really right now...
I'm just very emotional.

708
00:37:59.986 --> 00:38:01.946
Um. I'm at really a loss.

709
00:38:02.613 --> 00:38:03.948
I'm very emotional.

710
00:38:04.031 --> 00:38:05.783
I'm just... I feel blessed.

711
00:38:05.908 --> 00:38:07.326
It was like Mardi Gras.

712
00:38:07.451 --> 00:38:09.745
They all went out to celebrate.

713
00:38:11.497 --> 00:38:15.126
And not only was it
Sean Combs acquitted.

714
00:38:15.209 --> 00:38:19.130
but Anthony "Wolf"
Jones was also acquitted.

715
00:38:19.213 --> 00:38:21.924
And. of course. "Shyne"
Barrow was convicted.

716
00:38:23.759 --> 00:38:25.469
Yeah. I spoke to Shyne.

717
00:38:25.594 --> 00:38:29.515
Shyne says. "Look.
he lied on the stand.

718
00:38:29.640 --> 00:38:31.017
He got people to lie for him.

719
00:38:32.560 --> 00:38:34.270
Puffy betrayed me."

720
00:38:35.062 --> 00:38:36.147
Those were his words.

721
00:38:36.939 --> 00:38:38.107
He went in there

722
00:38:38.190 --> 00:38:40.029
and he lied about the fact
that he didn't have a gun.

723
00:38:40.109 --> 00:38:43.738
Everybody knew pretty
much that Combs had a gun.

724
00:38:45.364 --> 00:38:47.325
When I found out the verdict.

725
00:38:47.450 --> 00:38:49.827
I was shocked and disappointed

726
00:38:50.619 --> 00:38:52.830
at our legal system.

727
00:38:52.913 --> 00:38:54.665
But I was relieved

728
00:38:54.790 --> 00:38:59.670
because I did not want to
be the guy that sent him to jail.

729
00:38:59.795 --> 00:39:03.215
I didn't want that
for my own safety.

730
00:39:03.341 --> 00:39:04.387
I was a child of hip-hop.

731
00:39:04.467 --> 00:39:06.802
I didn't deserve
this. I was a victim.

732
00:39:06.886 --> 00:39:08.054
I wanted justice.

733
00:39:09.930 --> 00:39:12.016
You know.
went to try and console

734
00:39:12.099 --> 00:39:13.559
Shyne's mother. grandmother.

735
00:39:13.684 --> 00:39:15.061
And...

736
00:39:15.186 --> 00:39:16.354
as we left that day.

737
00:39:16.479 --> 00:39:18.856
there were still
supporters outside.

738
00:39:18.939 --> 00:39:22.693
But no one really cared
about him at that point.

739
00:39:22.777 --> 00:39:24.320
He was yesterday's news.

740
00:39:26.864 --> 00:39:29.367
When he was
convicted. I got angry

741
00:39:29.492 --> 00:39:30.701
because there are families

742
00:39:30.826 --> 00:39:33.579
that are giving young
people to you. Puffy.

743
00:39:33.704 --> 00:39:36.999
and you have a responsibility
to these young people

744
00:39:37.083 --> 00:39:38.417
on your record label.

745
00:39:40.294 --> 00:39:43.381
I think it was an attempt
to take down another rap star.

746
00:39:43.506 --> 00:39:45.883
And I think that. clearly.
we proved his innocence.

747
00:39:46.008 --> 00:39:48.594
He was. in fact.
a victim that night.

748
00:39:48.719 --> 00:39:50.683
And I think you're going
to see great things from him

749
00:39:50.763 --> 00:39:52.056
for the future.

750
00:39:53.516 --> 00:39:54.979
I think it was pretty
clear to most people

751
00:39:55.059 --> 00:39:57.728
that at the very least.
he hung him out to dry.

752
00:39:57.853 --> 00:40:00.356
And at the very worst.
Shyne took the fall.

753
00:40:05.069 --> 00:40:07.446
There was
the City College incident.

754
00:40:08.823 --> 00:40:10.533
Steve Stoute incident.

755
00:40:11.700 --> 00:40:13.911
and the nightclub shooting.

756
00:40:13.994 --> 00:40:17.873
He's getting this
reputation of being a Teflon Don.

757
00:40:17.957 --> 00:40:20.543
And that is a pattern
that we continue to see.

758
00:40:20.626 --> 00:40:23.087
is that even when things
are really. really bad

759
00:40:23.212 --> 00:40:24.130
for other people.

760
00:40:24.255 --> 00:40:26.215
for Puffy. just a blip.

761
00:40:28.467 --> 00:40:31.303
He was getting
away with things for so long.

762
00:40:31.887 --> 00:40:33.848
But I believe...

763
00:40:35.141 --> 00:40:36.600
the truth will
always find its way.

764
00:40:36.684 --> 00:40:37.684
even in the dark.

765
00:41:01.375 --> 00:41:04.128
Thanksgiving break
in November 2023.

766
00:41:04.253 --> 00:41:05.253
I got a call.

767
00:41:10.926 --> 00:41:12.803
"Your rape was caught on tape."

768
00:41:14.138 --> 00:41:18.392
I said. "What do you mean
my rape was caught on tape?"

